media-drive-create - Media Drive Creation

USAGE:
    media-drive-create

DESCRIPTION:
    Create and configure a new media drive with encryption and ZFS.
    Prompts for drive, volume name, source host, and LUKS passphrase.

INPUT:
    - Media Drive (disk device)
    - Media Volume Name (ZFS volume name)
    - Media Source Host (for ZFS snapshot send)
    - Media LUKS Passphrase (encryption password)

PROCESS:
    - Remove existing labels and create GPT
    - Create Linux partition
    - Setup LUKS encryption
    - Create ZFS pool with compression
    - Send ZFS snapshots from source host

EXAMPLES:
    media-drive-create
